[Aroor (State Assembly constituency)|Aroor]] || 80.47\n|-\n| 114 || [[Konni (State Assembly constituency)|Konni]] || 70.07\n|-\n| 133 || [[Vattiyoorkavu (State Assembly constituency)|Vattiyoorkavu]] || 62.66\n|}\n\n== Results in a glance==\nThe results at a glance are given below:\n=== By alliance ===\nBoth the [[Left Democratic Front (Kerala)|LDF]] and the [[United Democratic Front (Kerala)|UDF]] won three seats each. The [[National Democratic Alliance|NDA]] could not win any seats. \n{| class=\"sortable\" width=\"25%\" cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"1\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; border: 2px #000000 solid; font-size: x-big; font-family: API PHONETIQUE\"\n|- valign=\"top\"\n! style=\"background-color:#666666; color:white\"| ||style=\"background-color:#666666; color:white\" |Alliance || style=\"background-color:#666666; color:white\" |Seats Contested || style=\"background-color:#666666; color:white\" |Seats Won || style=\"background-color:#666666; color:white\" |Seat Change \n!style=\"background-color:#666666; color:white\" |Vote %|| style=\"background-color:#666666; color:white\" |Swing\n%\n|-\n\n| style=\"background-color:{{United Democratic Front (Kerala)/meta/color}}\" |&nbsp;\n! style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[United Democratic Front (Kerala)|UDF]]\n| align=\"right\" | 06 || align=\"right\" | 03 || align=\"right\" | {{decrease}}02 \n| align=\"right\" | 38.68 || align=\"right\" | {{decrease}}1.78 \n|-\n\n| style=\"background-color:{{Left Democratic Front (Kerala)/meta/color}}\" |&nbsp;\n! style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[Left Democratic Front (Kerala)|LDF]]\n| align=\"right\" | 06 || align=\"right\" | 03 || align=\"right\" | {{increase}}02 \n| align=\"right\" | 37.97 || align=\"right\" |  {{increase}}1.53 \n|-\n\n| style=\"background-color:{{National Democratic Alliance (India)/meta/color}}\" |&nbsp;\n! style=\"text-align:left;\" |[[National Democratic Alliance|NDA]]\n| align=\"right\" | 06 || align=\"right\" | 00 || align=\"right\" | 00 \n| align=\"right\" | 21.63 || align=\"right\" | {{decrease}}0.09 \n|-\n\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color:#666666; color:white\"| '''Total'''!! align=\"right\" style=\"background-color:#666666; color:white\"| 06!! align=\"right\" |\n|\n|\n|\n|}\n\n=== Party-wise ===\nEach of the [[Communist Party of India (Marxist)|CPI(M)]] and the [[Indian National Congress|INC]] won in two seats. The remaining two seats were bagged by the [[Nationalist Congress Party|NCP]] and the [[Indian Union Muslim League|IUML]] respectively.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable collapsible\" width=\"35%\" cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"1\" style=\"text-align:center; border-collapse: collapse; border: 2px #000000 solid; font-size: x-big\"\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#DB0000 ; color:white;\"|LDF\n! style=\"background:#DB0000 ; color:white;\"|SEATS\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#0269A4; color:white;\"|UDF\n! style=\"background:#0269A4; color:white;\"|SEATS\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"background:#FF9933; color:white;\"|NDA\n! style=\"background:#FF9933; color:white;\"|SEATS\n|-\n|[[Communist Party of India (Marxist)|CPI(M)]]\n|width=\"3px\" style=\"background-color: {{Communist Party of India (Marxist)/meta/color}}\"|\n|02\n|[[Indian National Congress|INC]]\n|width=\"3px\" style=\"background-color: {{Indian National Congress/meta/color}}\"|\n|02\n|[[Bharatiya Janata Party|BJP]]\n|width=\"3px\" style=\"background-color: {{Bharatiya Janata Party/meta/color}}\"|\n|00\n|-\n|[[Nationalist Congress Party|NCP]]\n|width=\"3px\" style=\"background-color: {{Nationalist Congress Party/meta/color}}\"|\n|01\n|[[Indian Union Muslim League|IUML]]\n|width=\"3px\" style=\"background-color: {{Indian Union Muslim League/meta/color}}\"|\n|01\n|\n|\n|\n|-\n|[[Left Democratic Front (Kerala)|LDF<br/>Independent]]\n|width=\"3px\" style=\"background-color: {{Left Democratic Front (Kerala)/meta/color}}\"|\n|00\n|[[United Democratic Front (Kerala)|UDF<br/>Independent]]\n|width=\"3px\" style=\"background-color