asabha]].\n\n{| class=\"sortable\" width=\"45%\" cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"1\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; border: 2px #000000 solid; font-size: x-big\"\n! style=\"background-color:#666666; color:white\" |Constituency\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"background-color:#666666; color:white\" |Member\n! style=\"background-color:#666666; color:white\" |Party\n! style=\"background-color:#666666; color:white\" |Alliance\n|----\n| [[Manjeshwaram (State Assembly constituency)|Manjeshwaram]]\n| [[M. C. Kamaruddin]]\n|\n| {{legend2|green|[[Indian Union Muslim League|IUML]]|border=solid 1px #AAAAAA}} \n| {{legend2|#0087BD |[[United Democratic Front (Kerala)|UDF]]|border=solid 1px #000000}}\n|----\n| [[Ernakulam (State assembly constituency)|Ernakulam]]\n| [[T. J. Vinod]]\n| \n| {{legend2|#00BFFF|[[Indian National Congress|INC]]|border=solid 1px #AAAAAA}} \n| {{legend2|#0087BD |[[United Democratic Front (Kerala)|UDF]]|border=solid 1px #000000}}\n|----\n| [[Pala (State Assembly constituency)|Pala]]\n| [[Mani C. Kappan]]\n|\n| {{legend2|#007FFF|[[Nationalist Congress Party|NCP]]|border=solid 1px #AAAAAA}}\n| {{legend2|#DB0000|[[Left Democratic Front (Kerala)|LDF]]|border=solid 1px #000000}}\n|----\n| [[Aroor (State Assembly constituency)|Aroor]]\n| [[Shanimol Usman]]\n| \n| {{legend2|#00BFFF|[[Indian National Congress|INC]]|border=solid 1px #AAAAAA}}\n| {{legend2|#0087BD |[[United Democratic Front (Kerala)|UDF]]|border=solid 1px #000000}}\n|----\n| [[Konni (State Assembly constituency)|Konni]]\n| [[K. U. Jenish Kumar]]\n|\n| {{legend2|#FF0000|[[Communist Party of India (Marxist)|CPI(M)]]|border=solid 1px #AAAAAA}}\n| {{legend2|#DB0000|[[Left Democratic Front (Kerala)|LDF]]|border=solid 1px #000000}}\n|----\n| [[Vattiyoorkavu (State Assembly constituency)|Vattiyoorkavu]]\n| [[V. K. Prasanth]]\n|\n| {{legend2|#FF0000|[[Communist Party of India (Marxist)|CPI(M)]]|border=solid 1px #AAAAAA}}\n| {{legend2|#DB0000|[[Left Democratic Front (Kerala)|LDF]]|border=solid 1px #000000}}\n|}\n\n== Assembly seat share post by-elections ==\n\nAfter the 2019 Kerala Legislative Assembly by-elections, the composition of 14th [[Kerala Legislative Assembly]] changed as per given below:\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; width:350px; height:75px; font-family:API-PHONETIQUE\"\n|-\n! style=\"background-color:#b0b0f4\" |[[United Democratic Front (India)|UDF]] !! style=\"background-color:#b0b0f4\" |[[Left Democratic Front (Kerala)|LDF]]!! style=\"background-color:#b0b0f4\" |[[National Democratic Alliance|NDA]]\n|-\n|style=\"background:{{United_Democratic_Front_(Kerala)/meta/color}}; width:30%;color:white\"|'''45'''\n|style=\"background:{{Left_Democratic_Front_(Kerala)/meta/color}}; width:30%;color:white\"|'''93'''\n|style=\"background:{{National_Democratic_Alliance_(India)/meta/color}}; width:30%;color:white\"|'''2'''  \n|}\n\nThe [[Kerala Niyamasabha]] is composed of 141 seats (140 elected and 1 nominated). After the byelections, the [[Government of Kerala]] has the support of 93 members.\n\n'''Total (141)'''\n\n'''[[Government of Kerala|Government]] (93)''' \n*'''[[Left Democratic Front (Kerala)|LDF]]''' (93)\n**{{Color box|#FF0000|border=darkgray}} [[Communist Party of India (Marxist)|CPI(M)]] (60)\n**{{Color box|#FF0000|border=darkgray}} [[Communist Party of India|CPI]] (19)\n**{{Color box|#138808|border=darkgray}} [[Janata Dal (Secular)|JD(S)]] (3)\n**{{Color box|#007FFF|border=darkgray}} [[Nationalist Congress Party|NCP]] (3)\n**{{Color box|#FF7F7F|border=darkgray}} [[Congress (Secular)|C(S)]] (1)\n**{{Color box|#CC6600|border=darkgray}} [[Kerala Congress (B)|KC(B)]] (1)\n**{{Color box|#00FF00|border=darkgray}} [[National Secular Conference|NSC]] (1)\n**{{Color box|#757575|border=darkgray}} [[Independent politician|IND]] (5)\n\n'''[[Official Opposition (India)|Opposition]] (45)'''\n*'''[[United Democratic Front (Kerala)|UDF]]''' (45)\n**{{Color box|#00BFFF|border=darkgray}} [[Indian National Congress|INC]] (21)\n**{{Color box|#007000|border=darkgray}} [[Indian Union Muslim League|IUML]] (18)\n**{{Color box|#B88A00|border=darkgray}} [[Kerala Congress (M)|KC(M)]] (5)\n**{{Color box|#CC6600|border=darkgray}} [[Kerala Congress (Jacob)|KC(J)]] (1)\n\n\n*'''[[National Democratic Alliance|NDA]]''' (2)\n**{{Color box|#FF9900|border=darkgray}} [[Bharatiya Janata Party|BJP]] (1)\n**{{Color box|#6E6E6E|border=darkgray}} [[P.C. George|KJ(S)]] (1)\n'''Others(1)'''\n** {{Colorbox|#000000|border=dark gray}} Nominated (1)\n\n== See also ==\n{{Portal|India}}\n* [[2016 Kerala Legislative Assembly election]]\n* [[Kerala Legislative Assembly]]\n* [[2019 Indian general election in Kerala]]\n* [[2019 elections in India]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://ceo.kerala.gov.in/ Chief Electoral Officer,Kerala]\n*[http://eci.nic.in/eci/eci.html Election Commission of India]\n*[http://udfkerala.org/ UDF Kerala]\n*[http://ldfkeralam.org LDF Keralam]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20160517184033/http://election.keralabjp.org/ NDA Kerala]\n\n{{Kerala Niyamasabha elections}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kerala Legislative Assembly by-elections 2019}}\n[[Category:By-elections in India|2019]]\n[[Category:State Assembly elections in Kerala|2019]]\n[[Category:2010s in Kerala]]\n[[Category:2019 State Assembly elections in India]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Kerala Legislative Assembly by-election}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=January 2020}}\n{{Infobox election\n| election_name = 2019 Kerala Legislative Assembly by-elections\n| country = India\n| type = parliamentary\n| ongoing = no\n| previous_election = 2016 Kerala Legislative Assembly election\n| previous_year = 2016\n| next_election = 2021 Kerala Legislative Assembly election\n| next_year = 2021\n| election_date = 23 September 2019 (1 seat) and 21 October 2019 (5 seats)\n| seats_for_election =     [[Manjeshwaram (State Assembly constituency)|Manjeshwaram]], [[Ernakulam (State assembly constituency)|Ernakulam]], 